8. app.py (Connecting all files)

from flask import Flask, render_template

app = Flask(__name__)

@app.route("/")
def home():
    return render_template(
        "welcome.html",
        name="Anand",
        is_topper=True
    )

@app.route("/about")
def about():
    return render_template("about.html")


if __name__ == "__main__":
    app.run(debug=True)

.................................................................................................
9. How it works (Flow)

User visits /
      ↓
Flask route in app.py
      ↓
render_template("welcome.html")
      ↓
welcome.html extends base.html
      ↓
base.html layout + welcome content
      ↓
Final HTML page shown

