1️⃣ Project Structure (How files are linked)

Your project should look like this:
Flask_Project
│
│ app.py
│
└── templates
      base.html
      feedback.html
      thankyou.html

Flask automatically looks for HTML files inside the templates folder.
...................................................................................................
1️⃣ app.py (Main Flask Application)

# Import Flask framework and required modules
from flask import Flask, render_template, request

# Create Flask application
app = Flask(__name__)

# Route for Home Page
@app.route("/")
def home():
    # When user opens http://127.0.0.1:5000/
    # Flask loads feedback.html page
    return render_template("feedback.html")  # home page


# Route for Feedback Form
# methods allow GET (open page) and POST (submit form)
@app.route("/feedback", methods=["GET", "POST"])
def feedback():

    # If form is submitted
    if request.method == "POST":

        # Get data from form input fields
        # name attribute in HTML connects here
        name = request.form.get("username")
        message = request.form.get("message")

        # Render thankyou.html page
        # Send variables to template using Jinja2
        return render_template(
            "thankyou.html",
            user=name,        # variable user = name
            message=message   # variable message = message
        )

    # If request method is GET
    # open feedback form page again
    return render_template("feedback.html")


# Run Flask server
if __name__ == "__main__":
    app.run(debug=True)   # debug=True auto reloads server

    ........................................................................................
2️⃣ base.html (Main Layout Template)

This file is the parent template used by other pages.

